Z_Cj36Z2Dq6pnUNi1QKbyqVk_PsJyoRu_D4-eavpvC_4jO69h3ZcP1XG3paeO7Pf9ofFY1gh937=
hg_puFEb-YKYS8C9QRbAQI51YAdvN2yImuX9T3xV3IBk7z9Hp6HQxgcXy94ew ) I have been=
 hoping for; my desk has four monitors, which makes even a 16=E2=80=B3 scre=
en a pain when I travel. This feature is good enough that I might have to c=
arve out some space in my carry-on for its bulk.

It=E2=80=99s also cost-competitive with two $1,600 Studio Displays, while d=
elivering an equivalent amount of screen space (5120=C3=971440 effective re=
solution vs 2 2560=C3=971440 effective resolution displays) in a drasticall=
y smaller footprint; it=E2=80=99s a fun accompaniment to the new Mac Mini:

( https://twitter.com/BenGeskin/status/1854654046050959529?ref_src=3Dtwsrc%=
5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1854654046050959529%7Ctwgr%5E229989f=
1ee375ff3de9a796754c97d47f194743e%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&ref_url=3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fchro=
me-headless.local%3A9222%2Fatomic )

It=E2=80=99s not perfect. For one thing, the foveated rendering used by the=
 Vision Pro means that only the part of the UI you are looking at is in foc=
us; this was a bit distracting for me, given that part of the reason I like=
 having so many monitors is that I like being able to see things out of the=
 corner of my eye. It=E2=80=99s also annoying to have a cord that isn=E2=80=
=99t connected to the Mac ; what I really want is a plastic (i.e. lighter) =
headset that just connects directly to the Mac, rendering any connectivity =
issues moot (although I didn=E2=80=99t experience any issues). This particu=
lar use case does justify the Vision Pro=E2=80=99s high resolution; it does=
n=E2=80=99t justify using metal and glass and having dedicated chips for an=
other computer and 12ms passthrough.

That noted, one thing that I was reminded of while trying this feature out =
is how fun the Vision Pro is to use once you get it on; the problem, as I n=
oted on today=E2=80=99s Dithering ( https://dithering.fm/ ) , is that putti=
ng it on is work. Then again, if you=E2=80=99re actually doing work, that=
